That means we've got a hard light source.

00:04:23.120 --> 00:04:25.480
How do the word
hard come about in photography first of all?

00:04:25.480 --> 00:04:28.020
You look at
that shadow line. See how it's a very hard,

00:04:28.020 --> 00:04:31.130
sharp line?
That's how the word hard light came. Because

00:04:31.130 --> 00:04:34.841
if it's a soft light
source, that shadow is what? Very soft. There's

00:04:34.841 --> 00:04:38.340
no hard
line on it. Okay, so if you see that there

00:04:38.340 --> 00:04:40.590
in the
corner, then you look and you see underneath

00:04:40.590 --> 00:04:42.900
the dash,
