00:05:53.080 --> 00:05:56.889
or still life photography or any other kind
of

00:05:56.889 --> 00:05:59.180
photography, because you're dealing with one
very common

00:05:59.180 --> 00:06:02.570
important element. That's light . Once you
understand

00:06:02.570 --> 00:06:05.710
light, no matter what you put in front of
that lens, it's

00:06:05.710 --> 00:06:09.330
the same. The only variable between that light
and that

00:06:09.330 --> 00:06:12.310
subject is what? It's really you. That's what
most

00:06:12.310 --> 00:06:15.680
photographers tend not to focus in on. It's
that it's you

00:06:15.680 --> 00:06:18.760
that makes the big difference, not the technology,
not

00:06:18.760 --> 00:06:21.080
the subject matter. It's what you you're bringing
to

00:06:21.080 --> 00:06:25.050
that. Because as photographers, we are story
tellers.

00:06:25.050 --> 00:06:27.360
And that's the really cool thing about photography.
And

00:06:27.360 --> 00:06:29.100
every time you go click, most photographers
don't

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:31.800
understand is that one important thing is
that click is the

00:06:31.800 --> 00:06:34.910
summation of everything you've done to that
point in

00:06:34.910 --> 00:06:39.020
time. For example, if we were to sit there
and say a

00:06:39.020 --> 00:06:44.090
